description: Stephen Raburn  updated his status. Boys will be boys. Like most men, I suspect, I can admit to participating in conversations about females of which I am not proud. During the throes of adolescence with hormones a-raging, acting on false bravado and cluelessness, locker room talk among the boys - each of us equally as awkward and inexperienced and trying to impress the others with exaggerated tales of exploits - probably sounded just as lewd at times as the video of Donald Trump circulating on social media this morning. But then we grew up. We were embarrassed and ashamed. By the time we reached adulthood and experienced true love and developed deep, meaningful friendships with women, and, certainly, by the time we married and brought daughters into the world, this kind of demeaning and disgusting talk about females was unfathomable.   The video of Trump and Billy Bush was from 2005. That’s been a few years. But Donald Trump was not a dumb kid trying to sound cool to his equally dumb kid buddies. By then, he was an adult. He was married. He had daughters. I can’t imagine any woman voting for this man for POTUS - or any man who has a daughter or ever loved a woman or had a mother, sister or any other important female in his life. Anything short of a landslide on Nov. 8 will be embarrassing. Stephen Stephen
